        Official Singles Chart on 9/12/2016

        9 December 2016 - 15 December 2016

        The Official UK Singles Chart reflects the UK’s biggest songs of the week, based on audio and video streams, downloads, CDs and vinyl, compiled by the Official Charts Company. The UK Top 40 is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 and MTV, the Top 100 is published exclusively on OfficialCharts.com. View the biggest songs of 2024 so far.

        "Rockabye" by Clean Bandit (featuring Sean Paul and Anne-Marie) remains at number 1 for a fifth straight week. This makes it Clean Bandit's longest-running number 1 single, surpassing the four weeks their former chart-topper "Rather Be" spent at the top in 2014 (from January 24, 2014- February 14, 2014). It's the third Top 10 this year for Sean Paul, as a featured artist, following Sia's "Cheap Thrills", and Little Mix's "Hair".
        The 59th Annual Grammy Awards nominations were announced on December 6, 2016. The ceremony will be held on February 12, 2017, to recognize the best recordings, compositions, and artists of the eligibility year, which runs from October 1, 2015- September 30, 2016. Some of the nominees are still currently on the Top 100 Official UK Singles Charts. The Chainsmokers have three nominations ("Best New Artist", "Best Pop Duo/Group Performance", and "Best Dance Recording" for their single 'Closer'). Sia also has three nominations ("Best Pop Duo/ Group Performance", "Best Pop Vocal Album", and "Best Song Written for Visual Media"). Justin Bieber has four nominations ("Album of the Year", "Song of the Year", "Best Pop Solo Performance", and "Best Pop Vocal Album"). Beyoncé has nine nominations. Drake, Kanye West, and Rihana have eight nominations.
        It's beginning to look a lot like Christmas as there are now 18 Christmas classics on the Official Singles Charts. "All I Want For Christmas Is You" by Mariah Carey is at number 6.

        jesy nelson: 6/14/1991 *not an avid bb follower during this time*

        hot 100: 1. paula abdul/rush, rush; 2. color me badd/i wanna *** you up; 3. extreme/more than words; 4. michael bolton/love is a wonderful thing; 5. r.e.m./losing my religion; 6. mariah/i don't wanna cry; 7. emf/unbelievable; 8. luther vandross/power of love; 9. black box/strike it up; 10. hi-five/i like the way (kissing game).

        i wouldn't become a hot 100 addict until later this year, but when jesy was born i was def into: paula abdul, color me badd, mariah and hi five. mariah @ this time, had her 1st 4 singles go to #1 *the single in this top 10 would be the 4th and last single from her debut album* and she had just tied the jackson 5's feat of being the 2nd act to have their 1st 4 singles go to #1. *she would later top j5 when her 5th consecutive single 'emotions' went to #1. j5 is still the only group to have their 1st 4 singles go to #1*.

        bb 200 albums chart: 1. paula abdul/spellbound; 2. n.w.a./n-4life; 3. r.e.m./out of time; 4. michael bolton/time, love and tenderness; 5. c & c music factory/gonna make you sweat; 6. mariah carey/*same name*; 7. new jack city soundtrack; 8. garth brooks/no fences; 9. a.b.c/coolin' @ the playground; 10. extreme/extreme II

        my fave album from this top 10 would def. be mariah's debut album. not too much going on in the u.s. music scene during this time from what i recall...but that's all gonna change when mj comes back in dec. of this year ;). *when i became a life long bb addict*

        Here are some of my observations from the UK charts this week:
        - Clean Bandit earn a fifth consecutive week at #1 with 'Rockabye', which now becomes their longest #1 single. I have mixed thoughts on this; I definitely like 'Rockabye', but I prefer 'Rather Be' much more.
        - 6 Christmas songs appear in the Top 40 this week, including the biggest climber in the Top 40, 'All I Want For Christmas Is You' by Mariah Carey (29-6). This is the highest the song has peaked since it reached #4 in 2007 & this is also the tenth consecutive year it has re-entered the Top 40.
        - The Rolling Stones earn their 12th #1 album with 'Blue & Lonesome' today. The rest of the Top 5 is: 'Together' by Michael Ball & Alfie Boe (#2), 'Glory Days' by Little Mix (#3), 'The Wonder Of You' by Elvis Presley (#4) & '24HRS' by Olly Murs (#5).
        - Zayn & Taylor Swift could get next week's highest debut with 'I Don't Wanna Live Forever', which is for the upcoming 'Fifty Shades Darker' movie. At the moment it's hard to determine where it will debut next week, as it has very strong sales right now (#1 on iTunes), but is not available on Spotify or YouTube & that will put it at a streaming disadvantage.
        - It was a good week for Rag'n'Bone Man, as he earned his first UK Top 10 single with 'Human' & he is the BRITS Critic's Choice Award winner for 2017.
        - From her X Factor performance last weekend, Zara Larsson is the highest new entry this week with 'I Would Like' at #21. The winner of the current X Factor series will be announced on Sunday night, also making them very likely to get at least a Top 10 debut next week.
        - Finally, there are just two weeks to go until the 2016 Christmas #1 is announced.
